# BBClaw Adapter — minimal config reference
#
# Only knobs without sensible defaults are listed below. Everything else is
# auto-configured by the adapter (ADAPTER_MODE=auto, listen :18080, sane
# timeouts, …); see internal/config/config.go for the full list of overridable
# escape hatches if you ever need them.
#
# Three usage profiles, copy the block(s) you need:

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Profile 1 — Agent endpoints only (no voice / no cloud relay)
# What you NEED: nothing. Empty .env works.
# What you'll get: /healthz, /v1/agent/drivers, /v1/agent/message.
# Driver auto-detection: claude-code/opencode if their CLI is on PATH;
#   ollama if 127.0.0.1:11434 listens; aider if `aider` is on PATH.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Pick which driver runs when a request omits "driver". Default = first
# registered (auto: claude-code).
# AGENT_DEFAULT_DRIVER=claude-code

# Per-driver overrides — only set if your binary path or model differs:
# AGENT_OPENCODE_BIN=/usr/local/bin/opencode
# AGENT_OPENCODE_EXTRA_ARGS=--model,deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro
# AGENT_AIDER_BIN=
# AGENT_AIDER_EXTRA_ARGS=
# OLLAMA_MODEL=llama3.2

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Profile 2 — Add voice (PTT → ASR → agent → TTS)
# Required: pick an ASR provider and a TTS provider, fill its keys.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ASR — pick one provider:
#
#   local              Run a local CLI on the captured WAV. Bring your own
#                      whisper / FunASR. Set ASR_LOCAL_BIN.
#   openai_compatible  POST to /v1/audio/transcriptions. Set ASR_BASE_URL,
#                      ASR_API_KEY, ASR_MODEL.
#   doubao_native      ByteDance OpenSpeech WS. Set ASR_WS_URL, ASR_APP_ID,
#                      ASR_API_KEY, ASR_RESOURCE_ID.
ASR_PROVIDER=openai_compatible
ASR_BASE_URL=https://api.openai.com
ASR_API_KEY=
ASR_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini-transcribe

# TTS — pick one provider:
#
#   doubao_native      ByteDance OpenSpeech WS (default). Set TTS_APP_ID,
#                      TTS_TOKEN. TTS_VOICE / TTS_CLUSTER have working defaults.
#   local_command      Run a local CLI on the text. Set TTS_LOCAL_BIN.
#   mock               No real synthesis (silent WAV). Useful for adapter
#                      smoke tests when you don't want to spin up TTS.
TTS_PROVIDER=doubao_native
TTS_APP_ID=
TTS_TOKEN=

# OpenClaw gateway — auth token only; URL defaults to ws://127.0.0.1:18789.
# Skip this whole section if you're not running OpenClaw locally.
OPENCLAW_AUTH_TOKEN=

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Profile 3 — Add cloud relay (cloud_saas firmware support)
# Auto-mode (default) starts the relay automatically when these are set.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# CLOUD_WS_URL=wss://your.cloud.host/ws
# CLOUD_AUTH_TOKEN=

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Production hardening (optional)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Bearer token required on every local HTTP request. Leave empty in dev.
# ADAPTER_AUTH_TOKEN=
